  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare two different fixationmethods for fractures of the
      wrist(distal radius fractures). We are comparing an external fixation
      (Hoffmann-II-non-bridging) vs. an internal fixation(Micronail). Primary endpoint is patient
      satisfaction as scored by the DASH-questionnaire.Secondary followup is X-rays, strength,
      PRWE-questionnaire.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
